						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I think many of the mode 7 racing games (like <em>F-Zero</em> and <em>Super Mario Kart</em>) use another mode for the horizon area, but not changing during the scanline.</div><br />SNES modes affect the entire screen, so I don't know how someone would accomplish that without either HDMA (writing to $2105 at a specific scanline, hence changing mode), or through $4209/420a (letting you pick a scanline in the register and when the raster gun hits that scanline, the code at the NMI vector is called, and NMI would change $2105).</div>

